    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen inside a formatted man file, for example `fhopen.2` and run `!man %` the output is not rendered correctly. \r\n\r\n<img width=\"1728\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-12-28 at 12 37 32\" src=\"https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/50372354/a16f7984-5c14-4e86-bac5-cc782843e18f\">\r\n\r\nThe directory is under my `MANPATH`.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`nvim --clean`\r\n\r\nopen any formatted `man` file like `fhopen.2`\r\n\r\n`:!man %`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nTo be able to read the formatted man page inside neovim like:\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1728\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-12-28 at 12 39 31\" src=\"https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/50372354/82a37e77-43e9-4699-ac98-f0014a980358\">\r\n\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.9.4 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.1700008891\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, version 9.0.2018, standard macOS vim (not brew or macports)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 14.2.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\niterm2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nmacports",
